issue(id="0011" status="review")
  title Support selectable clean auth profiles at bootstrap time
  user-story
    as-a scrubs user working across personal and organization contexts
    i-want to choose which clean auth profile a guest should use at bootstrap time
    so-that a fresh guest can come up with the right host-sourced credentials without forcing one token or account context to serve every repo
  premise.
    Scrubs currently has a strong clean-auth path for GitHub CLI and Codex:
    host-side credentials are the source of truth, bootstrap seals guest-local
    artifacts, and clean wrappers materialize those credentials only on demand.

    That model works well for a single GitHub token, but GitHub fine-grained
    personal access tokens are owner-scoped. In practice this means a token
    that works well for personal repositories may not be the right token for
    organization-owned repositories, especially when the organization requires
    approval, limits repository scope, or expects the token to be created for
    the organization as the resource owner.

    Scrubs therefore needs a way to select among multiple host-side auth
    sources when bootstrapping a guest. GitHub is the immediate motivation,
    but the design should be open to other clean auth domains where a user may
    legitimately want distinct personal, work, or environment-specific
    profiles.
  acceptance-criteria
    criterion Scrubs has a documented model for multiple selectable clean auth profiles rather than assuming a single GitHub token source.
    criterion A bootstrap-time path exists to choose which GitHub token source a guest should use, without requiring manual in-guest login ceremony.
    criterion The selected profile remains compatible with the existing sealed clean-auth design, including `gh` usage and the HTTPS Git helper path.
    criterion The configuration model is understandable for users who want at least personal and work profiles, including how host-side secrets are named and how a guest chooses between them.
    criterion The design does not regress the default simple path for users who only need one clean auth profile.
  review-items
    item(status="covered").
      Profile selection now supports an explicit bootstrap argument and a
      settings fallback. `just bootstrap <instance> <profile>` selects the
      profile for the current guest, while `SCRUBS_CLEAN_AUTH_PROFILE`
      remains available as the default-setting path. The built-in default
      profile name is `personal`.
    item(status="covered").
      Host-side GitHub secret naming now follows a profile-first convention.
      The operator helpers store tokens in macOS Keychain services such as
      `scrubs-gh-token-personal` and `scrubs-gh-token-work`, and bootstrap
      resolves those conventional names first while still tolerating the
      legacy single-token `scrubs-gh-token` path for compatibility.
    item(status="open").
      Decide how broadly the profile model should generalize beyond GitHub,
      especially for other clean-side auth domains that may also want
      distinct personal, work, or environment-specific profiles.
